- Total expenditures refer to the total amount spent by each department; 
- Department heads are responsible for managing their respective departments' budgets; 
- The budget year 2023 refers to the fiscal year ending on December 31, 2023; 
- The expenditure count represents the number of times each department has spent money in a given year.

- The comparison across consecutive years allows for analysis of financial trends and patterns within each department; 
- The inclusion of both expenditure and budget data enables the evaluation of financial management and planning; 
- A left join is used to account for departments that may not have any expenditure or budget data for the specified years.
